findings.recommendation:
Add a ref to track if notes have been manually loaded to prevent the effect from overwriting:

const hasLoadedMore = React.useRef(false);

React.useEffect(() => {
  if (project.notes && !hasLoadedMore.current) {
    setAllNotes(project.notes);
  }
}, [project.notes]);

const handleLoadMore = async () => {
  const moreNotes = await handleFetchNotes('project', project.id, { append: true });
  if (moreNotes && moreNotes.length > 0) {
    hasLoadedMore.current = true;
    setAllNotes(prev => [...prev, ...moreNotes]);
  }
};

Alternatively, combine local state with pagination state management in the hook to avoid this duplication entirely.

